444
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,100
for human development

445
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:29,466
Chapter 6

446
00:19:29,466 --> 00:19:32,233
shows us how to recognize and cultivate wisdom

447
00:19:32,233 --> 00:19:34,066
through choosing the right people

448
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,500
and training our minds skillfully

449
00:19:37,366 --> 00:19:40,366
Chapter 7 reveals what complete freedom looks like

450
00:19:40,366 --> 00:19:42,200
not withdrawal from life

451
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:44,533
but engagement without attachment

452
00:19:45,366 --> 00:19:48,666
Chapter 8 teaches us to focus on what actually matters

453
00:19:48,666 --> 00:19:50,500
instead of getting lost in impressive

454
00:19:50,533 --> 00:19:53,666
but meaningless activity Chapter 9

455
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:56,600
helps us understand how destructive patterns develop

456
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:57,533
gradually

457
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:01,266
and how to break them before they break us

458
00:20:02,033 --> 00:20:05,500
Chapter 10 grounds everything in our shared humanity

459
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,800
we all want happiness and safety

460
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,400
and that recognition

461
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:11,933
becomes the foundation for wise action

462
00:20:14,466 --> 00:20:16,033
remember from our first deep dive

463
00:20:16,033 --> 00:20:18,333
how mind precedes all things

464
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:23,366
today we've seen what happens when you master your mind

465
00:20:24,266 --> 00:20:27,000
you stop being a prisoner of your own patterns

466
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:29,500
you cross to the further shore

467
00:20:30,766 --> 00:20:33,566
this week try to apply Chapter Six's wisdom

468
00:20:33,566 --> 00:20:35,500
identify one person in your life

469
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:37,100
who cares enough about your growth

470
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:38,900
to give you honest feedback

471
00:20:39,066 --> 00:20:40,866
then actually ask for it

472
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:42,900
not about what you're doing wrong

473
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:46,366
but about what you're not seeing clearly

474
00:20:47,166 --> 00:20:49,166
the Dhammapada isn't meant to be read once

475
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:52,400
and understood these are principles to return to

